  "title": "Warehouse Admin Personnel",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a reliable and detail-oriented <strong>Warehouse cum Admin Personnel</strong> to join our team. This dual-role position combines warehouse operations with administrative support, ensuring smooth inventory management and efficient office coordination. The ideal candidate is organized, proactive, and able to balance hands-on tasks with clerical responsibilities.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>Warehouse Operations</p><ul><li>Receive, inspect, and store incoming goods.</li><li>Pick, pack, and prepare orders for delivery.</li><li>Maintain accurate stock records and conduct regular inventory checks.</li><li>Ensure warehouse cleanliness, safety, and compliance with company standards.</li><li>Coordinate with logistics providers for timely shipments and deliveries.</li></ul><p>Administrative Support</p><ul><li>Handle data entry, filing, and documentation related to warehouse activities.</li><li>Prepare delivery notes, invoices, and other relevant paperwork.</li><li>Assist in updating inventory systems.</li><li>Support procurement and liaise with suppliers when needed.</li><li>Provide general office administrative support (e.g., answering calls, managing correspondence).</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Prior experience in warehouse operations and/or administrative work preferred.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word) and basic inventory systems.</li><li>Strong organizational skills with attention to detail.</li><li>Ability to multitask and work independently in a fast-paced environment.</li><li>Good communication and teamwork skills.</li></ul><p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>",
